# React & Next.js Patterns

- Use **functional components** only.
- Prefer **server components** by default; use `"use client"` only when needed (hooks, interactivity, React Query).
- Colocate component-specific logic in the same file or extract to **custom hooks** in `lib/hooks/`.
- Use **Link** from `next/link` for internal navigation; use `paths.ts` or route strings for hrefs (e.g. `/trips`, `/trips/[slug]`).
- Keep components focused: presentational components in `components/`, reusable UI in `components/ui/`.
- Use existing UI primitives (`Button`, `TripCard`, etc.) before adding new ones; follow the same style (Tailwind + brand tokens from `globals.css`).

## Data in components

- For trips data, use **useTrips** from `lib/hooks/useTrips.ts` (wraps React Query). Do not call `tripsApi` directly from components.
- Handle loading and error states in the UI (skeletons, messages). Do not leave loading/error unhandled.
